cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about deep learning-based object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on deep domain adaptive object detection, which involves adapting a detector trained on one domain to another domain where the training and test data may have different distributions. This topic is closely related to transfer learning (cs.LG) and domain adaptation (cs.AI). Additionally, object detection is often used in multimedia applications (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO), which further support these potential sub-categories.
